# Optional first-run convenience only.
# Any key set here is moved into the macOS Keychain on first launch and is never
# persisted by the app. You can also paste keys into the in-app panel instead.
# Never commit real keys — .env is gitignored; this template must stay blank.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
OPENAI_API_KEY=
GROQ_API_KEY=
# Gemini accepts either name (GEMINI_API_KEY takes precedence):
GEMINI_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# --- Ralph loop <-> Slack (optional) ---
# One Slack app / bot token does both jobs:
#   1. loop.sh & loop-issues.sh push phone pings on blocks & stops (scripts/notify.sh).
#   2. When the build agent BLOCKS a card it asks you first (scripts/ask-human.sh);
#      reply in-thread with a number or free text to redirect it, or let it block.
# Setup: create a Slack app -> add bot scopes chat:write + channels:history
# (groups:history for a private channel) -> install -> invite the bot to the
# channel -> copy the xoxb- token and the channel ID (Cxxxx, not the #name).
# Unset = both features are silent no-ops; the loop runs exactly as before.
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=
SLACK_CHANNEL=
# ASK_TIMEOUT=900   # seconds the agent waits for a reply at a block before blocking.
#                   # Keep it well under loop.sh's ITER_TIMEOUT (default 1800s) — the
#                   # wait counts against the iteration budget. Raise both together.
# ASK_POLL=20       # seconds between reply checks
